<button class="accordion">What temperature should water be to prevent legionella?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The primary method used to control the risk from legionella is water temperature control. Water services should be operated at temperatures that prevent legionella growth. Hence, hot water storage cylinders (calorifiers) should store water at 60°C or higher.</p>
